The '''EDP Peştera Wind Farm''' is located in [[Peștera]] a commune in the [[Constanţa County]] of [[Dobruja]]. Costing €200 million, the wind farm consists of 30 three-bladed Danish [[wind turbine]]s, each capable of generating 3 [[megawatts]] (MW) of power, giving a total output of 90 MW.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bursa.ro/edp-a-finalizat-parcul-eolian-de-la-pestera-99036&s=companii_afaceri&articol=99036.html|title=EDP a finalizat parcul eolian de la Peştera|date=2010-10-21|work=Bursa|language=Romanian|accessdate=2010-10-21}}</ref> The EDP Peştera Wind Farm is the sister project of the [[EDP Cernavodă Wind Farm]], a 138 MW wind farm located {{convert|10|km|mi}} west of the Peştera farm close to the [[Cernavodă Nuclear Power Plant]] and the [[Danube – Black Sea Canal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zf.ro/companii/pestera-si-cernavoda-noile-sate-eoliene-din-dobrogea-7510776|title=Peştera şi Cernavodă, noile "sate eoliene" din Dobrogea|date=2010-10-20|work=Ziarul Financiar|language=Romanian|accessdate=2010-10-21}}</ref>

The wind farm is owned by [[EDP Renováveis]], the [[renewable energy]] branch of the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] conglomerate [[Energias de Portugal]].

