'''John Sinclair''' [[Order of Australia|AO]] (born 13 July 1939) received the [[Global 500 Roll of Honour]] award in 1990,<ref name="global500">
Global 500 Forum: [https://web.archive.org/web/20020718182712/http://www.global500.org/ViewLaureate.asp?ID=351] (archived webpage)
</ref> and was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 1993.<ref name="goldman">
Goldman Environmental Prize: [http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/165 John Sinclair] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071204050941/http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/165 |date= 4 December 2007 }} (Retrieved on 15 November 2007)
</ref> 
<ref name="johnsinclairtrust">John Sinclair Trust for Conservation [http://www.sinclair.org.au/ Official Website]</ref>
Born in [[Maryborough, Queensland]], Australia, Sinclair fought for thirty years to protect [[Fraser Island]], and succeeded in stopping logging of the island's rainforest, and sand mining by multinational corporations.

