The '''mud blenny''' (''Parablennius lodosus'') is a species of [[combtooth blenny]] found in the western [[Indian Ocean]].  This species reaches a length of {{convert|4|cm|in}} [[fish measurement|SL]].<ref>{{FishBase species |genus= Parablennius|species= lodosus| month = February | year = 2013}}</ref>

