{{short description|Power line between islands in Japan}}
{{unreferenced|date=July 2010}}

'''Osaki Channel Crossing''' is a [[power line]] crossing the [[Seto Inland Sea]] south of Yoshina, [[Takehara, Hiroshima|Takehara]] in Japan, which was built in 1997 and runs to the Ozaki Power Plant. The Ozaki Power Plant is owned by [[Chugoku Electric Power Company]] and is situated on an island on the Inland Sea. It has a span width of 2145 metres.

As at [[Chūshi Powerline Crossing]], towers with three crossbars are used. Their height is 223 metres, just 3 metres less than that of the Chūshi Powerline crossing, making them the second-tallest [[Transmission tower|electricity pylons]] in Japan.

